## Database Models (Prisma)

```prisma
model Usuario {
  id      Int           @id @default(autoincrement())
  email   String        @unique
  name    String?
  coments Comentarios[]
}

model Destinos {
  id          Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
  nome        String?
  descricao   String  @unique
  coordenadas String  @unique
  imagem      String  @unique
}

model Comentarios {
  id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  title     String
  content   String?  @db.Text
  published Boolean  @default(false)
  author    Usuario  @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id])
  authorId  Int
}

model Admin {
  id       Int    @id @default(autoincrement())
  password String @unique
  email    String @unique
}
```

---

## Frontend Routes

| Path | Component | Description |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| `*` (default) | `<Home>` | Landing / home page |
| `/get` | `<Get>` | Data fetching page |
| `/login` | `<Name>` (Login) | Login page |

---

## Architecture Patterns

### Backend Layered Architecture
```
Route → Controller → Service → Prisma (DB)
```
- **Routes** (`src/routes/`): Define HTTP endpoints, delegate to Controllers
- **Controllers** (`src/controllers/`): Orchestrate request/response logic
- **Services** (`src/services/`): Business logic and all Prisma queries

> Always keep Prisma queries inside `services/`. Controllers must NOT query the DB directly.

### Frontend Component Pattern
- Components live in `src/components/`
- Routing defined centrally in `src/routes.tsx`
- Use functional components with React hooks

---

## Environment Variables

See `backend/.env.example` for required variables. Key vars:
- `DATABASE_URL` — Prisma connection string
- `PORT` — Express server port

---

## Running the Project

### Backend
```bash
cd backend
npm run dev       # tsx --watch server.ts
```

### Frontend
```bash
cd frontend
npm run dev       # vite dev server
```

### Database (Docker)
```bash
cd backend
docker-compose up -d
```

### Prisma
```bash
# Generate client after schema changes
npx prisma generate

# Run migrations
npx prisma migrate dev --name <migration_name>

# Open Prisma Studio
npx prisma studio
```

---

## Coding Conventions

- **Language**: TypeScript everywhere (strict mode preferred)
- **Imports**: Use `.js` extension in backend imports (ESM)
- **Exports**: Named exports preferred over default exports
- **Async**: Always use `async/await`, not `.then()` chains
- **Error handling**: Use try/catch in controllers; let errors bubble up from services
- **Env access**: Always via `process.env.*` with dotenv loaded at entry point
- **Generated files**: Never edit files in `generated/` manually

---

## Key Files to Know

- `backend/prisma/schema.prisma` — Source of truth for DB models
- `backend/src/config/database.ts` — Prisma client singleton
- `backend/server.ts` — Express app boot
- `frontend/src/routes.tsx` — All client-side routes
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` — Root React component
